SolarBeam is released under the GPL license, see the LICENSE file. In
addition, the program uses a number of third party libraries under various
licenses:

* astronomy algorithms for solar position

The code in libsolar/SolarOrbit/Orbit.cs is a port of the javascript code
offered at http://www.srrb.noaa.gov/highlights/sunrise/calcdetails.html.

* the program's collection of geographic locations

The collection was generated using data obtained freely from
http://www.world-gazetteer.com. Copyright by Stefan Helders
www.world-gazetteer.com. This concerns location names and positional
coordinates. Timezone data per location was compiled by SolarBeam.

* zoneinfo

This is timezone data generated from the zoneinfo timezone database in the
Public Domain, see http://www.twinsun.com/tz/tz-link.htm.

* libpublicdomain

This is the "PublicDomain" distribution from
http://publicdomain.codeplex.com/, pruned of everything not relating to
timezone/dst functionality and slightly hacked. The distribution is released
under Public Domain, as is this stripped down version.

* NDesk.Options.dll

This is the NDesk Options command line option parser, see
http://www.ndesk.org/Options. It is released under the MIT/X11 license, see
http://www.opensource.org/licenses/mit-license.php.

* nunit.framework.dll

This is the NUnit testing framework, see http://www.nunit.org. It is released
under its own license, see http://www.nunit.org/index.php?p=license&r=2.4.8.

* icons

The icons used in the program are from the "oxygen" icon theme in KDE and were
obtained freely from http://www.oxygen-icons.org/. It is released under the
LGPL, see http://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl.html.

Some icons have also been used from http://openclipart.org, under Public
Domain.
